    "As before, the discussion seems to be focused on the political actors that shape policies, i.e.",
    "actors like the government, Boris Johnson, Ed Miliband, and others.",
    "The sentiment analysis suggests some expected political divisions (e.g.",
    "the Net Zero Scrutiny Group attracts negative sentiment from The Guardian and neutral sentiment from The Times) and some less expected ones (Johnson is associated with positive sentiment in the Mail but also The Guardian, and negative from the other two newspapers).",
